711898f-a.text:
W. 28th Street, north side, west from 9th to 10th ~Svenues,
showing several private dwellings, a Public Bath and a factory
facing the lower portion of helsea Park, In the latter appears
a portion of P.S. No. 33. Note the 9th 'Svenue ''E1' structure
overhead.
View No.2 is northeastward to show the several small buildings
forming the N.W. corner and the ~mpire State Building across
their roofs. At the right are tenements at the N.E. corner.
The two set back buildings at the left bear No's 4O3 and 405
W. 28th Street.

710354f-c.title: Manhattan: 9th Avenue - 28th Street (West)
710354f-c.text:
(1)
Ninth Avenue, west side, south from W. 28th Street, sho ing
the easterly side of Chelsea Park. Across same appears the four
story factory of Eny-Scheerer and Co.
Beyond is the 10 story structure occupied by Heywood, Strasser
and Voight Litho.Co. This is at the S.W. corner of W. 26th Street.
June 28, 1928
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTICNS.
(2)
Same as above, looking southward,after demolition of
'Etg~'. This is a closer view.
P. L. Sperr  April 18, 1941
NO REPRODUCTIONS
(3)
9th Avenue, north side, between 26th and 27th, same as
two preceding views from a different angle.
P. L Sperr  April 18, 1941
NO REPRODUCTIONS
